title: Grateful Dead Live at McArthur Court, University Of Oregon on 1981-08-06
description:
Set I
Jack Straw
Friend Of The Devil >
El Paso
Loser
New Minglewood Blues
Peggy-O >
Little Red Rooster
Deal
Set II
Feel Like A Stranger
Scarlet Begonias >
Fire On The Mountain
Estimated Prophet >
Eyes Of The World >
Drums > *
Space >
The Other One >
Stella Blue >
Around & Around >
Good Lovin'

Encore:
It's All Over Now Baby Blue


Comment
Jerry Garcia - Guitar
Bob Weir - Guitar
Brent Mydland - Keyboards
Phil Lesh - Bass
Bill Kreutzmann - Drums
Mickey Hart - Drums
Ken Kesey - The Thunder Machine *
Zane Kesey - The Thunder Machine *
Ken Babbs - The Thunder Machine *

reviews.review_text: Down to Eugene to see the Grateful Dead Crisp soundboard from 8/16/81, not 8/6.

8/16/1981 A couple of shots of whiskey, these Oregon fillies start looking good. 

The drummers held this tour/year together. Great set list. Jack Straw sets the tone. Oh how I miss a good Loser in the middle of the first set. Solid second set complete with that nasty improv jamming that is so special.

This is a time when the Dead didn't mail in the slow ballads. Later in the decade, there were more throw away slower songs that never quite took off as the Dead had to come up with new covers to keep Jerry interested. 

1981 was also the last year before cocaine took the beat to a faster then necessary pace and everything was hurried and frenzied.
this tasty SB is an 8/16/81 Show, NOT 8/6/81 This is mislabeled. The date should be 8/16/81 and it's much better than the only other SB Source >> gd1981-08-16.sbd.unknown.32019.flac16
